iv><div class="t mbe7 xbd h4 yf98 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—&quot;In order to strengthen our con-</div><div class="t m27a xb4 h4 y18fa ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fidence in God, Christ teaches us to address </div><div class="t m33b xb4 h4 y1672 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him by a new name, a name entwined with </div><div class="t m4c9 xb4 h4 yf5a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the dearest associations of the human heart. </div><div class="t m2c6 xb4 h4 y18fc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He gives us the privilege of calling the in-</div><div class="t m2cf xb4 h4 y16b1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">finite God our Father. This name, spoken </div><div class="t m5e2 xb4 h4 yb30 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to Him and of Him, is a sign of our love and </div><div class="t m907 xb4 h4 yb32 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trust toward Him, and a pledge of His re-</div><div class="t m87f xb4 h4 y173f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gard and relationship to us. Spoken when </div><div class="t md3 xb4 h4 yc22 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">asking His favor or blessing, it is as music </div><div class="t mdfc xb4 h4 y289 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in His ears. That we might not,tthink it </div><div class="t m291 xda h4 y687 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">preiumption to call Him by this name, He </div><div class="t m15f xb4 h4 y179e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">has repeated it again and again. He desire&apos;s </div><div class="t m69c xda h4 y183d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">us to become familiar with the appellation.&quot; </div><div class="t m564 xb4 h30 y1656 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">—Christ&apos;s Object Lessons </div><div class="t m244 x40 h4 y268 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(1941 ed.), pages </div><div class="t m316 xb4 h4 y16ff ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">141, 142. </div><div class="t m7d6 xe h35 y182d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m589 x26 h35 y6aa ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Since God is our &quot;Father,&quot; what </div><div class="t m7ad xb4 h35 y16ba ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">relationship do we sustain to Him? 